  "text": "The Kubernetes admission webhook processing chain comprises several interconnected layers that manage dynamic admission control:\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nThe admission webhook processing chain in Kubernetes is implemented across multiple packages with a clear separation of concerns:\n\n### 1. Generic Webhook Dispatcher (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/)\n\nThe generic package provides the foundational webhook infrastructure:\n\n- **webhook.go**: Contains the `Webhook` struct that serves as the abstract admission plugin with infrastructure for both mutating and validating webhooks. The `NewWebhook()` function initializes webhooks with configuration management and dispatcher factories. The `Dispatch()` method coordinates webhook execution by fetching hooks from the source and delegating to the specific dispatcher.\n\n- **interfaces.go**: Defines critical interfaces:\n  - `Dispatcher` interface: Implemented by both mutating and validating dispatchers, defines the `Dispatch()` method that processes admission requests\n  - `Source` interface: Lists dynamic webhook plugins from configuration\n  - `WebhookInvocation` struct: Encapsulates how to call a webhook with resource/kind information\n  - `VersionedAttributeAccessor` interface: Manages versioned attributes for different API versions\n\n### 2. WebhookAccessor Abstraction Layer (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/accessors.go)\n\nThe `WebhookAccessor` interface provides a common abstraction for both mutating and validating webhooks:\n\n- **WebhookAccessor interface**: Defines methods for accessing webhook properties (name, rules, failure policy, namespaceSelector, objectSelector, sideEffects, timeout, etc.) and retrieving RESTClient connections.\n\n- **mutatingWebhookAccessor**: Implements WebhookAccessor for v1.MutatingWebhook, provides cached access to REST clients and compiled CEL matchers\n\n- **validatingWebhookAccessor**: Implements Webhook